  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators describe a novel technique for GB fundus retraction.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      few methods are available for gall bladder (GB) retraction in SILC to replace the usage of
      ancillary ports imitating retraction from conventional technique, e.g. trans-parietal
      stitches mini-loop retractor , a Kirschner wire . This technical note describes a novel way
      to retract the gall bladder fundus.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
